title: Indian and Chinese Forces Clash on Border, India Says
description: The Indian army said Monday that Indian and Chinese security forces clashed on the countries’ disputed border alongside a northeastern Indian state last week.

title: Lockerbie Bombing Suspect to Make First U.S. Court Appearance
description: A Libyan explosives expert is expected in a Washington courtroom Monday, charged with assembling the device that blew up Pan Am Flight 103 over Lockerbie, Scotland in 1988.

title: Peru's New President Proposes Early Elections After Protests
description: President Dina Boluarte proposed bringing forward the elections following deadly protests in support of her ousted predecessor.

title: Teen Palestinian Girl Killed During Shootout Between Israeli Forces, Militants
description: The Israeli military says it is investigating the death, which adds to the highest death toll in the West Bank since 2006.

title: Second Iranian Protester Executed as Government Shifts its Response
description: Iran’s government has moved toward swift punishment against a few people accused of violent crimes against security forces while holding out the possibility of concessions to other Iranians.

title: Zelensky and Biden Discuss Ukraine's Grid as Country Scrambles to Restore Power
description: Ukraine rushed to restore power supplies following the latest round of Russian attacks, while President Volodymyr Zelensky spoke with President Biden after a flurry of weekend diplomacy aimed at strengthening sanctions on Russia.

title: China Halts Location Tracking App as Covid Restrictions Fall
description: China is dismantling a symbol of one of the world’s sternest Covid-19 containment regimes: its nationwide mobile tracking app.

title: In U.S. Bid to Bolster Pacific Sway, Postal Service Has a Say
description: Negotiations to renew agreements with three Pacific island allies face resistance from the cash-strapped USPS, testing U.S. commitment to the region where China is trying to project more influence.

title: Germany Is Short of Workers, but Its Migrants Are Struggling to Find Jobs
description: A magnet for asylum seekers, Germany isn’t attracting enough qualified newcomers and is struggling to train the new arrivals.
